74
00:05:17,150 --> 00:05:21,416
Ooh, he's a big 'un!
Where did he learn to whittle like that?

75
00:05:21,587 --> 00:05:23,521
How many drinks
have you had?

76
00:05:23,690 --> 00:05:25,885
Not nearly enough.

77
00:05:34,567 --> 00:05:38,196
So... How are you?

78
00:05:38,371 --> 00:05:39,736
I'm great.

79
00:05:39,906 --> 00:05:43,034
And Daniel Boone, is he a nice guy?

80
00:05:43,209 --> 00:05:45,541
His name is Aidan.

81
00:05:47,046 --> 00:05:50,777
- Where is your sense of humor?
- Where is your wife?

82
00:05:50,950 --> 00:05:55,387
Guarding her bid on the silent auction.
She's got her eye on a beige chair.

83
00:05:55,555 --> 00:05:58,251
Everything in my apartment
is now beige.

84
00:05:58,424 --> 00:06:00,892
Beige is bullshit.

85
00:06:01,060 --> 00:06:03,085
I thought you wanted beige.

86
00:06:03,262 --> 00:06:07,926
Yeah, well... It doesn't quite fit.

87
00:06:08,101 --> 00:06:10,763
- Have you got a smoke?
- I quit.

88
00:06:10,937 --> 00:06:13,167
We always used to share
a cigarette together.

89
00:06:13,339 --> 00:06:16,775
We did a lot of things
that were bad for me together.

90
00:06:16,943 --> 00:06:19,104
I have a secret
to tell you.

91
00:06:22,648 --> 00:06:27,585
It's not working.
I'm getting out.

92
00:06:28,688 --> 00:06:30,918
If you know anyone
who's interested...

93
00:06:31,090 --> 00:06:37,723
You should keep that to yourself.
No one wants that information.

94
00:06:45,004 --> 00:06:47,097
- Big's leaving his wife.
- No!

95
00:06:47,273 --> 00:06:50,504
- He told me at the furniture show.
- What was he doing there?

96
00:06:50,676 --> 00:06:52,906
- Drinking and leaving his wife.
- Oh, my God.

97
00:06:53,079 --> 00:06:55,741
- Let's just say it. You won.
- Was there a contest?

98
00:06:55,915 --> 00:06:59,749
There's always a contest with an ex.
It's called "Who'll Die Miserable?".

99
00:06:59,919 --> 00:07:03,116
- What did he say?
- He said, "It's not working out."

100
00:07:03,289 --> 00:07:07,885
Then he leaned in and said, "If you
know anyone who's interested..."

101
00:07:08,060 --> 00:07:12,861
You don't know anyone
who is interested. He's married.

102
00:07:13,032 --> 00:07:15,557
- I'm aware of that.
- Why is he telling you?

103
00:07:15,768 --> 00:07:18,293
To save postage on his newsletter?

104
00:07:18,471 --> 00:07:20,166
- What are you gonna do?
- Nothing.

105
00:07:20,339 --> 00:07:23,672
- She's not gonna do anything.
- You're starting to bug me.

106
00:07:23,843 --> 00:07:26,903
How dare he say that to you?
Married men never leave their wives.

107
00:07:27,079 --> 00:07:30,276
Even if he did, I have no intention
of doing anything for two reasons -

108
00:07:30,483 --> 00:07:33,611
I have a great boyfriend,
and I'm not insane.

109
00:07:33,786 --> 00:07:37,483
Let's order. What do winners order?

110
00:07:37,657 --> 00:07:42,356
- Didn't you feel like punching him?
- No. It was too sad or something.

111
00:07:42,528 --> 00:07:45,861
- I would have punched him.
- No, it is sad.

112
00:07:46,065 --> 00:07:48,625
How long has he been married?
Seven months?

113
00:07:48,801 --> 00:07:50,564
The seven-month itch.

114
00:07:50,736 --> 00:07:55,036
That's what happens when people
jump into relationships too quickly.

115
00:07:55,208 --> 00:07:59,338
I resent that. Trey and I
are nothing like Big and Natasha.

116
00:07:59,512 --> 00:08:01,776
Don't listen to her.
She's mid-break-up.

117
00:08:01,948 --> 00:08:05,475
- Thanks for the update.
- Trey and I really love each other.

118
00:08:05,651 --> 00:08:07,312
Who wants to split a Rubin?

119
00:08:07,520 --> 00:08:12,514
I'm meeting his mother this week,
and if all goes well...

120
00:08:12,692 --> 00:08:14,523
If all goes well what?

121
00:08:14,694 --> 00:08:17,663
Trey is this close to proposing.
I can feel it.

122
00:08:17,830 --> 00:08:19,559
Oh, my God. Really?

123
00:08:19,732 --> 00:08:22,166
You've just met.
I've had pairs of pantyhose longer.

124
00:08:22,335 --> 00:08:25,361
It's not logical. This is love.

125
00:08:25,538 --> 00:08:28,871
It's not logical.
It's right, in my heart. I feel it's right.

126
00:08:29,075 --> 00:08:31,976
OK, whatever.

127
00:08:34,580 --> 00:08:37,549
So, how did he look?

128
00:08:45,591 --> 00:08:47,559
OK. I'll take it.

129
00:08:48,895 --> 00:08:53,457
As Miranda looked around,
she realized the contest was over.

130
00:08:53,633 --> 00:08:56,124
Steve was the ex that was
going to die alone and miserable.

131
00:08:56,335 --> 00:09:01,068
- You can't live here.
- It's not that bad.

132
00:09:01,274 --> 00:09:04,368
It's not that bad?
It's the doorway to hell.

133
00:09:04,544 --> 00:09:07,536
There's gotta be a better place.
I'll help you look.

134
00:09:07,713 --> 00:09:10,910
- Guilt?
- Probably.

135
00:09:11,083 --> 00:09:16,578
I broke up with him, and he's got
no money, no savings, no nothing.

136
00:09:16,822 --> 00:09:21,350
There should be a city-funded
break-up housing for those in need.

137
00:09:21,527 --> 00:09:22,789
Really?

138
00:09:22,962 --> 00:09:28,298
A big orphanage where old boyfriends
could think about what they did wrong

139
00:09:28,467 --> 00:09:33,461
and cry themselves to sleep
in a clean, safe environment.

140
00:09:33,639 --> 00:09:35,971
You think you don't really
want him to move away?

141
00:09:36,142 --> 00:09:37,973
It's not that simple.

142
00:09:38,144 --> 00:09:41,477
My head tells me it's time
for him to leave, but the idea of him

143
00:09:41,647 --> 00:09:47,085
moving into a basement apartment
in West Shit Street breaks my heart.

144
00:09:47,253 --> 00:09:52,122
It's a common belief that women use
the left, emotional side of their brain

145
00:09:52,291 --> 00:09:55,124
and men the right, more logical side.

146
00:09:55,294 --> 00:09:57,387
But is it really that cut and dry?

147
00:09:57,563 --> 00:09:59,827
When it comes to affairs of the heart,

148
00:09:59,999 --> 00:10:02,968
there's a battle between
what we know and what we feel.

149
00:10:03,135 --> 00:10:05,433
What do you do in a situation

150
00:10:05,605 --> 00:10:08,574
that leaps back and forth
between the left and right side?

151
00:10:08,741 --> 00:10:13,974
In relationships, is it smarter
to follow your heart or your head?

152
00:10:14,146 --> 00:10:17,047
This is Trey when he graduated
from medical school.

153
00:10:17,216 --> 00:10:20,515
Later that week, Charlotte met
the head and heart of Trey's family -

154
00:10:20,686 --> 00:10:22,176
his mother,
Bunny MacDougal.

155
00:10:22,388 --> 00:10:26,222
Trey, you look so cute
in a cap and gown!

156
00:10:26,392 --> 00:10:31,193
That was before we jumped
in the fountain and hell broke loose.

157
00:10:31,364 --> 00:10:32,729
What's next -
boy scout snaps?

158
00:10:32,898 --> 00:10:35,833
Count your blessings I didn't bring
the one on the bearskin rug.

159
00:10:36,035 --> 00:10:39,869
You'll have to excuse her.
She's a bit of a camera nazi.

160
00:10:40,039 --> 00:10:42,940
If you insist on dragging us
down memory lane,

161
00:10:43,109 --> 00:10:47,102
I'm getting a real drink.
Excuse me, a Glenlivet rocks, please.

162
00:10:47,279 --> 00:10:51,147
Maybe you should have a red wine
instead. Better for the heart.

163
00:10:52,351 --> 00:10:54,546
- All righty.
- Red wine.

164
00:10:54,720 --> 00:10:58,156
Thomas, we'd love some more
nibbly cheese things.

165
00:10:58,324 --> 00:11:00,554
- Very good, ma'am.
- Thank you.

166
00:11:00,726 --> 00:11:04,719
He's older than water,
but never forgets a martini.

167
00:11:06,732 --> 00:11:09,701
- Do you play tennis?
- Mm-hm.

168
00:11:09,869 --> 00:11:11,894
I like her.

169
00:11:12,104 --> 00:11:14,004
Join the club.

170
00:11:14,173 --> 00:11:19,042
- What are you two doing tonight?
- We've got reservations at Cloche.

171
00:11:19,211 --> 00:11:25,013
I was there last week. Disappointing
crab and the host was rude.

172
00:11:26,619 --> 00:11:29,918
Maybe you should go
to Côte Basque instead.

173
00:11:30,089 --> 00:11:31,556
All righty.

174
00:11:31,757 --> 00:11:34,021
Charlotte was impressed
with Bunny's technique.

175
00:11:34,193 --> 00:11:36,787
Trey had been looking forward
to Cloche all week.

176
00:11:36,962 --> 00:11:42,525
Meanwhile, downtown, Samantha was
entertaining Adam Ball, a film editor

177
00:11:42,702 --> 00:11:47,503
who made a living cutting coming
attractions for film companies.

178
00:11:47,673 --> 00:11:48,697
Coming.

179
00:11:48,874 --> 00:11:50,341
I'm coming.

180
00:11:53,846 --> 00:11:56,508
Oh, man!

181
00:11:56,682 --> 00:11:58,149
You give good head.

182
00:12:03,956 --> 00:12:07,414
I'm dating a guy
with the funkiest tasting spunk.

183
00:12:13,899 --> 00:12:16,163
And she's never coming back.

184
00:12:16,335 --> 00:12:18,826
Sorry, but who else
can I talk to about this?

185
00:12:19,004 --> 00:12:22,235
- Might I suggest, no one?
- You're my girlfriends. Help me.

186
00:12:22,475 --> 00:12:25,205
- Have you ever had this problem?
- Not really.

187
00:12:25,411 --> 00:12:29,313
But I have to admit it's never been
a trip to Baskin-Robins.

188
00:12:29,482 --> 00:12:33,350
This guy is very sour. Like asparagus
gone bad or something.

189
00:12:33,519 --> 00:12:35,510
Can I cancel my rice pudding?

190
00:12:35,688 --> 00:12:38,555
Beautiful guy, great in bed,
it's so disappointing.

191
00:12:38,724 --> 00:12:42,751
It's like a bad bottle of Beaujolais
Nouveau the first day of season.

192
00:12:42,962 --> 00:12:46,898
It's to do with nutrition. I once dated
a smoker. It affected how his tasted.

193
00:12:47,066 --> 00:12:49,933
They should put that
on the pack to cut back sales.

194
00:12:50,102 --> 00:12:52,468
Maybe there's something he could eat
to make it sweeter.

195
00:12:52,671 --> 00:12:56,801
- You should write to Martha Stewart.
- Dear Martha, funky spunk, help!

196
00:12:56,976 --> 00:13:00,707
Dear funky spunk, try a hint of mint.

197
00:13:00,880 --> 00:13:04,475
It's not just asparagus.
It's asparagus and something else.

198
00:13:04,650 --> 00:13:06,777
I know: Clorox.

199
00:13:06,952 --> 00:13:10,353
- At least it'll get your whites whiter.
- This is serious. I almost gagged.

200
00:13:10,523 --> 00:13:12,320
- That is serious.
- What am I gonna do?

201
00:13:12,491 --> 00:13:16,427
- Just don't give him head again.
- I never even thought of that.

202
00:13:16,595 --> 00:13:18,722
Casual head is back now?

203
00:13:18,898 --> 00:13:21,560
It's fine. He's healthy,
and I don't swallow.

204
00:13:21,734 --> 00:13:25,568
As long as you and the center
for disease control are fine with it.

205
00:13:25,738 --> 00:13:28,366
He loves getting head,
but what man doesn't?

206
00:13:28,541 --> 00:13:33,444
If the come-situation were reversed,
do you think men would go near it?

207
00:13:33,612 --> 00:13:35,807
Maybe.
If it tasted like beer.

208
00:13:38,217 --> 00:13:42,051
Miranda came home to something
that was even harder to swallow.

209
00:13:42,221 --> 00:13:45,247
You have one new message.

210
00:13:46,258 --> 00:13:48,692
Hi. If this is Steve's number...

211
00:13:48,861 --> 00:13:53,924
This is Barbara. We met last night.
I'm the advertising exec.

212
00:13:54,099 --> 00:14:00,060
Steve, if this is you, call me.
I'd love to go to a movie sometime.

213
00:14:00,239 --> 00:14:03,504
Today, 12:22 pm.

214
00:14:04,510 --> 00:14:07,968
And on an answering machine
across town...

215
00:14:09,281 --> 00:14:12,216
You have one new message.

216
00:14:12,384 --> 00:14:17,083
Hi, it's me. I need to talk to you
about what I said the other day.

217
00:14:17,256 --> 00:14:20,020
It's important.
You know my cell number.

218
00:14:20,192 --> 00:14:23,286
The right side of my brain
told me to delete it.

219
00:14:23,462 --> 00:14:25,293
But I left it.

220
00:14:25,497 --> 00:14:27,556
It's important.
You know my cell number.

221
00:14:27,733 --> 00:14:30,702
Seven playbacks later,
I invited an impartial judge.

222
00:14:30,870 --> 00:14:32,599
- Well?
- You should have punched him.

223
00:14:32,771 --> 00:14:35,968
He wants to get back together, right?
That's the tone.

224
00:14:36,141 --> 00:14:38,939
The "Hi" and the "It's important".
Is that what it means?

225
00:14:39,144 --> 00:14:43,604
We will never know. They still
don't know who killed Kennedy.

226
00:14:44,950 --> 00:14:48,078
- What should I do?
- It's obvious what you want to do

227
00:14:48,254 --> 00:14:53,317
or you wouldn't listen to it and what
happened to the sane part of you?

228
00:14:53,492 --> 00:14:57,053
I don't know. After the fifth playback
he got in a little.

229
00:14:58,097 --> 00:15:00,463
- I hate my machine.
- Yeah.

230
00:15:00,666 --> 00:15:02,861
I hate mine too.

231
00:15:03,035 --> 00:15:07,267
Steve got a message from a girl
desperate for him to go to a movie.

232
00:15:07,473 --> 00:15:11,307
- Already? He's still on your couch.
- I know. It's amazing.

233
00:15:11,477 --> 00:15:14,503
A 34-year-old guy
with no money and no place to live

234
00:15:14,680 --> 00:15:16,807
because he's single,
he's a catch.

235
00:15:16,982 --> 00:15:19,576
